OL,7,F"This was a matter of life and death
OL,8,Fand we feel it was neglect. There was
OL,9,Fno note of her suicide attempts."
OL,11,FPolice officer Timo Luoto gave
OL,12,Fevidence during the inquest. He
OL,13,Fexplained how it was "one word against
OL,14,Fanother" when it came to investigating
OL,15,Fwhether the police or prison guard had
OL,16,Ffailed to voice Ayesha's thoughts of
OL,17,Fharming herself.
OL,19,FThe jury concluded a verdict of
OL,20,Fsuicide, with the medical cause of
OL,21,Fdeath being by hanging.
